<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1059" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1059">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.112 Er 4/4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister in temporary charge of the
                                    Embassy at Constantinople</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-30"><hi rend="italic">November 30,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Instructs to insist upon immediate reply to the representations made by
                            the embassy in regard to the deportation of Erickson from Elbassan and
                            to report the result to the Department by cable.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>